  "texts": [
    "In the Actor-Critic learning framework, both the actor and critic can be approximated by the DNNs with learnable parameters [207].",
    "Different from the traditional AI techniques that focus on the data analysis to handle specific tasks, GAI aims at learning the distribution and pattern of training samples in a USL manner [208].",
    "According to the learned statistical properties of training data, GAI can generate the new samples similar to the original training samples, and present them in diverse formats, such as images and videos.",
    "Apart from the content generation, GAI also exhibits the powerful inference and modeling capabilities, enabling its wide applications in diverse domains, such as wireless communications [209].",
    "In the following, four representative GAI models are discussed, and their model structures are presented in Figure 10.• Generative adversarial networks (GANs)."
  ]
}